node.text:
On Earth Day, I launched my new brand @cozeco , made of timeless essentials that work effortlessly with your everyday style. In case you missed my IG LIVE, watch how I style-out our first collection, ‘BLOOM’, to show you just how easy it is to wear the pieces and seamlessly add them to your existing wardrobe. I love these pieces, and it is so exciting to show you how I personally wear each one. 
 
Follow along to get inspired and #getcoze

node.text:
#CapitalOnePartner This past year has been all about making the most with what you've got. At the beginning of quarantine, we were cooking like crazy. I thought maybe I'd come out of this year as an incredible home chef. But no. The cooking and cleaning burnout got real real and we started ordering in A LOT to make our days less hectic. The food would arrive and we would sit down to eat with no intention or care about the meal. It made me sad like it was just so anticlimactic and mundane so it was time for me to shake things up a bit. We may be limited on where we can eat dinner, but that doesn’t mean we can’t switch up HOW we do it. With the help of @capitalone, I got to elevate an everyday takeout meal! The little bit of extra effort you put into getting dressed or setting the table or even using your fancy dishes can really give you an elevated feel at home during this difficult time. I got to access and share my creativity, which makes me feel whole.
 
Putting in some work to make yourself happy, will make you a better mom, dad, wife, husband, friend, employee, boss … whatever. Help yourself and then go help someone else. You’ll feel better every time. I can almost promise that! #ElevateTheEveryday Special Thanks to @gigis_la for the delicious food. Y’all MUST go or pick up from there if you’re in LA. XX

node.text: THEY WERE AMAZING!! We maybe overcooked them a touch, but they were so good. I did it! I'm feeling a lot of shine. Thanks to everyone who watches and leaves comments. You guys are so encouraging, and I love encouragement. Should Timmy and I have our own cooking show? I mean, I think we should. Is there anyone from the Food Network watching and thinking we shouldn't? Because they should be fired immediately. Deborah, you are fired. Sorry. Pack up your sh*t.

node.title: Wait What With Whit: Chocolate Soufflé Part 2

node.text: Hiiiiiiiii. Hope everyone is having a great Thursday! I decided to spend some time with my @renttherunway fall collection and style it with my own wardrobe. Head to renttherunway.com to become a member to rent or purchase! Do you like these kinds of styling videos? If so, I’ll do more! 😽

node.text: I LOVE Chocolate Soufflé. When you are a person who does not love love a lot of food, the ones you do love, you love hard. Never in a million years, however, would I attempt to make one on my own, but that was before WWWW. Now, I'm trying all sorts of sh*t and loving it. Thanks for joining for this installment. I am using the "New York Times Bittersweet Chocolate Soufflé” recipe. Check out next week's to see how it turned out. Let me know in the comments what your favorite dessert is. PEACE!

node.title: Wait What With Whit: Chocolate Soufflé Part 1

node.text: My goal today was to beat my rally record of 7.  It's important to set goals! Watch the full video to see if I do it! I am definitely sticking with tennis and am going to play until I can't anymore. Learning how to do all these new things has changed the way I look at my life. The world has so many different things to offer, and I don't have to be an expert at anything to enjoy them. I strongly encourage all of you out there to never stop trying new things.

node.title: Wait What With Whit: Tennis Part 2

node.text: I always thought tennis wasn't for me because I didn't grow up playing. But F that! I love it. I'm just starting out and not very good yet, but I'm having so much fun. Unlike yoga, where my mind can wander, I'm always thinking about my form, footwork, or where I want to hit the ball.  By the time my hour is over, I genuinely feel like I have taken a break from the 19 billion things I have to do in a day. Thank Tennis!! What do you guys do to take a mental breather from your days?

node.text:
Before quarantine, I was on my way to becoming the ""never get in the pool mom"". I don’t want to be that mom. No judgment, but it’s not that cold and my hair will be ok. Letting go with these boys is more important. Plus, I’m nasty at dunking and it would be a crime to deprive everyone of my vicious throw-downs. I will put you on a poster quick ( Timmy just taught me what that was). 

Are you a “go in the pool” mom or “hang by the chairs” mom?

We all know that). 

Are you guys “read the instructions” types or “use the force” types?

node.text:
I LOVED this one. For you creatives out there who need to have that itched scratched, potting these cute little guys really hits the spot. I encourage you to give it a try. I can see myself enjoying these on my own, away from Timmy's comments, being creative and zen and alone for six consecutive seconds without someone asking me a question or cleaning a dish or putting in a new garbage bag! Is anyone else going nuts?!??!? 

(Deep Breath)

I'm fine now. Seriously, this was nice. But also seriously, let me know if you are going nuts out there in the comments. Thanks!

node.text:
omg, what a day!!! He woke up to donuts and decorations (a Rosenman tradition), had a SUN CELEBRATION at school where we walked him through each year of his life and then we hosted a park party for his new class at school, and came home for some ribs, baked potatoes and ice cream cake with family for Sonny and @paigemport shared birthday.

While Timmy was reading books to Sonny last night and I finally sat down in silence at my computer, I started balling. At first, I thought it was cause I was tired and overwhelmed from the planning and hosting but then I realized it wasn’t that. I actually felt organized and loved the hosting aspect more than usual so I didn’t really know why I was a ball of emotions... Sonny then called for me to lay with him before bedtime. It took him about 30 minutes to get comfy and then he landed right on my chest and fell asleep within 10 seconds. I literally started weeping again. Like ugly cried- I could feel it. I was caressing his head and telling him how much I loved him like a lunatic. Life happens in the blink of an eye. I wasn’t tired, I was grieving. Grieving Sonny’s toddler years, grieving the losses of 3 miscarriages, and my dad. It felt like a really complicated mix of sadness and happiness until I walked out of Sonny’s room and into Timmy’s arms- exactly where I need to be. Grieving but always growing.

node.text:
Leveling with you each week about where I’m at on my life-long mental health quest has kept me accountable. I notice my energy and mood amplify, the more I talk about and take notice of where I’m at so I thought it could be helpful to keep the conversation going around health and wellness overall. It’s so important to have these convos and I’ve been really enjoying recording these solo episodes.

In this week’s episode of #WITHWHIT, I give you a look inside the ins and outs of my daily routine: basically how I start and end each of my days. I truly am a creature of habit, or at least I try to be. Within the past year and a half during the pandemic, I came to quickly realize that routines can be life-changing. For a lot of us, I’m sure the pandemic completely altered our routines and we had to learn how to create and adapt to new ones, which can be hard and takes time to adjust. Having a routine in the morning can set the tone for the rest of your day, and establishing a routine at night can prepare you to leave the stress of the day behind you and – hopefully – help you achieve a good night’s sleep. I also share my thoughts on social media and what helps me keep my physical health in check.

I hope you guys have been loving listening to these episodes with just me sharing stuff with you all. Let me know your routines in the comments below as I am always looking for more ways to live my best life!  AND be sure to tune in - link is in my bio. Xx
